TITLE: Dem. Sen. Murphy questions whether law enforcement should be funded in states that refuse to enforce gun laws
SUMMARY: Sen. Chris Murphy, D-Conn., said that 60% of counties in the U.S. refuse to enforce state and federal gun laws, calling it a "growing problem in this country."

TITLE: White House’s former ‘disinformation czar’ Nina Jankowicz registers as a foreign agent
SUMMARY: Nina Jankowicz, who briefly headed the Department of Homeland Security's Disinformation Governance Board, is now registered as a foreign agent, according to documents.

TITLE: Supreme Court Justice Amy Coney Barrett faces calls to recuse herself from LGBTQ case over Christian faith
SUMMARY: Justice Amy Coney Barrett's Christian faith and alleged ties to the group People of Praise are again called into question before the Supreme Court is set to hear an LGBTQ-related case.

TITLE: Florida AG says it’s ‘not rocket science’ why so many Americans are flocking to Sunshine State
SUMMARY: Republican Florida Attorney General Ashley Moody celebrated Florida's leadership and support of police while discussing why so many people are flocking to the Sunshine State.

TITLE: Schiff won’t say whether he’d comply with GOP subpoena, will ‘consider the validity’
SUMMARY: Rep. Adam Schiff, D-Calif., would not state whether he'd comply with a potential subpoena from Republicans and slammed Rep. Kevin McCarthy as having no "core set of beliefs."

TITLE: Clyburn says decision to stay in leadership is ‘biblical' to him, despite Pelosi’s call for ‘new generation’
SUMMARY: House Majority Whip Rep. James Clyburn said Sunday that his decision to retain a leadership position in the House Democratic Conference is "biblical" to him.

TITLE: Dem Gov. Polis declines to endorse Biden’s call for ‘assault weapons’ ban
SUMMARY: During an appearance Sunday on NBC News's "Meet the Press," Democratic Colorado Gov. Jared Polis declined to endorse President Biden’s call for an "assault weapons" ban.

TITLE: Fauci has a 'completely open mind' about COVID-19 lab leak theory, says evidence 'strongly' points elsewhere
SUMMARY: Dr. Anthony Fauci says he has a "completely open mind" when it comes to the origins of COVID-19 but argues that the scientific evidence strongly points away from a lab leak.

TITLE: Whole Foods under fire after announcing Maine lobster will be pulled from shelves at stores nationwide
SUMMARY: Whole Foods announced that it will no longer sell Maine lobster at stores after the Marine Stewardship Council and Seafood Watch pulled their support for the Maine industry.

TITLE: Biden admin scrambles to track $20B in Ukraine aid as House Republicans warn of audits
SUMMARY: President Biden's administration has tracked just 10% of the weapons sent to Ukraine, and Republicans in Congress are threatening audits and more aggressive oversight.

TITLE: Trump deems Kanye West a ‘seriously troubled man’ who 'just happens to be Black' after Mar-a-Lago trip fallout
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump says "Fake News went CRAZY" after he helped a "seriously troubled man, who just happens to be black," referring to Kanye West.

TITLE: FIRST ON FOX: Pence heading back to New Hampshire; will Trump hold first 2024 rally in December?
SUMMARY: Former Vice President Mike Pence is returning in two weeks to New Hampshire, an early nominating state, as he builds toward a likely 2024 White House run.

TITLE: Republicans, ahead of House takeover, look to zero in on Biden admin's handling of border crisis
SUMMARY: House Republicans are looking to ramp up the pressure on the Biden administration when they take control of the House of Representatives early next year.

TITLE: Trump's former US ambassador to Israel blasts meeting with Ye, Nick Fuentes: 'You are better than this'
SUMMARY: Jewish leaders are slamming former President Trump after he hosted a dinner in Florida this week that included rapper Ye and controversial political activist Nick Fuentes.

TITLE: Biden says family 'not having any' 2024 conversations in Nantucket
SUMMARY: President Biden said on Saturday that his family were celebrating rather than having conversations about a 2024 presidential bid while on vacation in Nantucket.

TITLE: White House slams Trump's dinner with Nick Fuentes, saying bigotry and hate have 'no place in America'
SUMMARY: The White House on Saturday took aim at former President Donald Trump for hosting white nationalist Nick Fuentes at his private club in Florida on Tuesday evening.

TITLE: Newsom won't challenge Biden in 2024, says he is 'all in' on president's re-election
SUMMARY: California Gov. Gavin Newsom is ruling out a challenge to President Biden for the 2024 Democratic nomination, telling Biden that he is "all in" on his re-election race.

TITLE: 'PANDEMIC OF VIOLENCE': Lightfoot's record on crime at the forefront of Chicago mayoral election
SUMMARY: The Chicago mayoral election features a number of candidates and comes amid a spike in crime as incumbent Mayor Lori Lightfoot seeks to retain her post leading the city.

TITLE: Matt Whitaker: "I don't have any reason to believe there's enough evidence to indict President Trump."
SUMMARY: Former acting Attorney General Matt Whitaker analyzes the Justice Department's special counsel probe and the legal fight to extend Title 42 expulsions.

TITLE: Joe and Hunter Biden go Black Friday shopping as Republicans prepare investigations into business deals
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden spent Black Friday shopping with his family, including his son Hunter Biden. They visited several stores on the Massachusetts island of Nantucket.
